17. LANGUAGE FUTURE

The JX language is still under development and constantly evolving.

New features are being planned, including performance improvements,
new commands and expansion of the execution system.

In the future, it will be possible to create more complex games using
engines built on top of the JX language, allowing more advanced projects
with greater control, interactivity and performance.

The goal of the language is to evolve from a simple console system into
a foundation capable of supporting more complete game development.
